  <front>
   <head>Slow, Slow, Fresh Fount</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="???">
     <l n="1" met="++++++--++">Slow, slow, fresh fount, keep time with my salt tears;</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+-+++-+-+">Yet slower, yet, O faintly, gentle springs!</l>
     <l n="3" met="+--+-+-+-+">List to the heavy part the music bears,</l>
     <l n="4" met="+++--+-+-+|+++--+---+">Woe weeps out her division when she sings.</l>
     <l n="5" met="++-+-">Droop herbs and flowers;</l>
     <l n="6" met="++-+-">Fall grief in showers;</l>
     <l n="7" met="--+--++-+--+">Our beauties are not ours. O, I could still,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+-+-+-+-+|-+-+--++-+">Like melting snow upon some craggy hill,</l>
     <l n="9" met="++++">Drop, drop, drop, drop,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+-+-+-+-+-+">Since nature's pride is now a withered daffodil.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
